nib.text:
A man was critically injured during a shooting in Lind-Bohanon, officials say.

Police responded to a report of a shooting in the 5100 block of Bryant Avenue North at 4:50 p.m.

Upon arrival, officers discovered a 19-year-old man with serious gunshot wounds, [KARE 11 reported](https://www.kare11.com/article/news/crime/minneapolis-police-teen-suffers-life-threatening-injuries-in-north-minneapolis-shooting/89-a8a0b91e-e4c7-4428-80aa-9ddafa3c048c).

Medics transported the victim to a local hospital.

According to a spokesperson from the MPD, the victim had been standing outside a car, talking to the passengers inside, when he was shot.

No arrests have been made. This investigation is ongoing.
